Figure 3. Lithium metal growth monitored by scanning electron microscopy images along plating. A PVDF or PAN solution was electrospun to form a nano-web scaffold on a copper foil electrode (PVDF#Cu or PAN#Cu). Both web scaffolds were prepared to have identical diameters of fibers as well as the same thickness of scaffold layers. (a) Top views of electrodes along plating with potential profiles. The amounts of lithium metal enough to fill out the voids of nano-web scaffolds were plated. (b) Cross-sectional views of lithium metal plated on PVDF#Cu and PAN#Cu, respectively. Lithium metal (7.5 mAh cm

 –2

) was plated on both electrodes.

